# 🧮 Calculator

**Intern:** Utkarsh  
**Task:** Level 2 — Task 1  
**File:** `calc.html`

## 📌 Overview
A fully functional scientific calculator built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript featuring a dark UI, expression history, keyboard support, and advanced operators.

## 🎯 Features
- ✅ Basic operations: Addition, Subtraction, Multiplication, Division
- ✅ Display screen for input and results
- ✅ CSS Grid used for button alignment
- ✅ Advanced: √ (square root), xʸ (power), % (percentage)
- ✅ Parentheses support ( ) with smart auto-close
- ✅ ANS button — reuse last result
- ✅ DEL to delete last character, C to clear all
- ✅ Expression history shown above current number
- ✅ Full keyboard support
- ✅ Error handling for invalid expressions

## 🖥️ Tech Stack
| Technology | Usage |
|------------|-------|
| HTML5 | Structure |
| CSS3 | Grid layout, dark theme |
| JavaScript | Logic, event listeners, evaluation |

## ⌨️ Keyboard Shortcuts
| Key | Action |
|-----|--------|
| `0–9`, `.` | Input digits |
| `+` `-` `*` `/` | Operators |
| `Enter` or `=` | Calculate |
| `Backspace` | Delete last |
| `Escape` | Clear all |

## 🚀 How to Run
Open `calc.html` in any browser — no installation needed.

